Episodes.Title: Young Guns Come Out Shooting
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: Eighteen aspiring chefs from across the country, 23-years-old or younger, begin the competition.

Episodes.Title: Temping the Meat
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: Both teams are put to the test as they take on their first dinner service, preparing dinner for boxing legend Mike Tyson and NASCAR driver Kurt Busch, as HELL'S KITCHEN opens its doors for the 300th time.

Episodes.Title: Come Hell or High Water!
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The chefs are challenged to replicate the very first challenge in HELL'S KITCHEN history - breaking down squid perfectly. Later, it's "Chicken Gate"; Gordon discovers the Blue Team served up raw chicken during Dinner Service.

Episodes.Title: Young Guns Going Big
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The chefs must make brunch for 60 hungry Caesars Palace employees.

Episodes.Title: Stirring the Pot
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: Both teams must work together to decipher recipes written in emojis. The newly formed teams must learn to work with their new brigades.

Episodes.Title: A Ramsay Birthday in Hell
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The restaurant is closed for chef Ramsay's daughter's 21st birthday party. Later, one more chef's mistakes will get them sent home.

Episodes.Title: If You Can't Stand the Heat...
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The chefs cook up a different international cuisine against a chef from the opposing team. The ingredients are selected over a game of soccer.

Episodes.Title: A Devilish Challenge
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The remaining chefs compete in a tag team relay race competition, in which they must cook entrées against the other team; five chefs face the first "Cook For Your Life" challenge of the season.

Episodes.Title: A Game Show From Hell
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: One team struggles to work together on its dish; a special charity dinner service.

Episodes.Title: More Than a Sticky Situation
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The chefs take on the blind taste test challenge with messy consequences; one team comes unglued during dinner service.

Episodes.Title: Swiping Right
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The chefs jump back into the dating game on hkchefsonly.com, hoping to swipe right on the perfect match of ingredients; the stakes are high during a special steak night dinner service; one team struggles with overcooking its dish.

Episodes.Title: All Hell Breaks Loose
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The competition is taken to a new level when the chefs have to prove they are worthy of a legendary black jacket; while some chefs quickly make the cut, others struggle to prove they have what it takes.

Episodes.Title: Social Media in Hell
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The chefs must create visually stunning dishes to impress chef Ramsay's Instagram followers.

Episodes.Title: Hell Hath No Fury...
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: A clash of egos causes tensions to run high; during a dinner service filled with sabotage, the chefs struggle to prove they have what it takes.

Episodes.Title: What the Hell
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The three remaining chefs must cook a five-course dinner service.

Episodes.Title: Two Young Guns Shoot it Out
Episodes.Actors: Gordon Ramsay, Jason Santos, Christina Wilson
Episodes.Plot: The final two chefs compete, after which the last chef standing wins the grand prize.
